a great butterscotch recipe my boyfriend loves butterscotch so i often bake these amazing butterscotch brownies but i would like something different i made a few different types of butterscotch cookies awhile ago and they were good but nothing beats the brownies please help the best butterscotch sauce in the world best served over ice cream in a puffed pastry shell butterscotch sauce ingredients cup packed brown sugar cup milk tablespoons light corn syrup tablespoons butter directions in a small saucepan stir together the brown sugar milk corn syrup and butter warm over low heat until smooth and butter is melted do not boil butterscotch cake ingredients ounce package yellow cake mix eggs cups butterscotch pudding cup butterscotch chips tablespoons white sugar cup blanched slivered almonds directions preheat oven to degrees f degrees c grease one x x inch jelly roll pan combine the cake mix eggs and butterscotch pudding spread the batter into the prepared pan and sprinkle with the butterscotch chips white sugar and slivered almonds bake at degrees f degrees c for minutes enjoy butterscotch cookie bars ingredients cup butterscotch chips cup butter eggs teaspoon vanilla extract cup all purpose flour teaspoon baking powder teaspoon salt cup brown sugar cup semi sweet chocolate chips cup chopped walnuts cup raisins optional directions place butterscotch chips and butter into a glass bowl heat in the microwave for about minutes stirring at second intervals until smooth set aside to cool until firm preheat the oven to degrees f degrees c grease a x inch pan in a large bowl beat the butterscotch chip mixture with eggs and vanilla until well blended combine the flour baking powder and salt stir into the batter until evenly mixed mix in the brown sugar chocolate chips walnuts and raisins spread the batter evenly in the prepared pan bake for minutes in the preheated oven just until the bars begin to pull away from the sides of the pan cut into squares while warm Haggis Cuisine